text: The Mosely-Woods House (a.k.a. Starling-Wilburn House) is a historic house in Yazoo City, Mississippi. ==History== The house was built circa 1860.John E. Ellzey, Yazoo, Gretna, Louisiana: Arcadia Publishing, 2014, p. 39 Two decades later, in 1880, it was acquired by William Mosely, a black landowner, from Ann Holt. ==Heritage significance== It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since June 25, 2005. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Mississippi Category:Houses in Yazoo County, Mississippi Category:National Register of Historic Places in Yazoo County, Mississippi
title: Mosely-Woods House
